Cleaning up, adding RSS feed: true to posts, modifying _quarto.yml per https://quarto.org/docs/websites/website-blog.html

Aug 11 2023, Pretoria

Lacks built-in RStudio option (add-in) for creating new posts

1. In posts directory create a subdirectory beginning with date e.g. 2023-08-11-foo
2. In that subdir best to copy the index.qmd from a previous post and modify (for now pending RStudio add-in)
3. Edit post (can do this in RStudio directly until happy)
4. in the weblog root dir run make (adds both the new post and the docs site to git)
5. git commit -am "foo message"
6. git push

That's it.

------

add .nojekyll (touch .nojekyll will suffice, empty file)

------

Change default _site to docs for use with GitHub Pages

To get started, change your project configuration to use docs as the output-dir. For example:

_quarto.yml
project:
  type: website
  output-dir: docs

-----


Creating GitHub repo required exxtra step git remote set-url origin git@github.com:JeffreyRacine/blog.git before push works

…or push an existing repository from the command line
git remote add origin https://github.com/JeffreyRacine/blog.git
git branch -M main
git push -u origin main



